(
  'nabla',
  'Nabla',
  'AI clinical documentation assistant for physicians',
  E'Nabla is an AI ambient clinical documentation tool that listens to the patient-physician conversation and automatically generates a structured clinical note, SOAP format, referral letter, or after-visit summary. The physician activates Nabla at the start of a consultation; the AI transcribes the conversation in real time and produces a draft note by the time the visit ends. The physician reviews, edits, and signs off  -  rather than typing notes from scratch or dictating into a separate system after the patient leaves.\n\nNabla integrates with the major EHR platforms including Epic, Cerner, and Athenahealth, inserting generated notes directly into the relevant patient record. This workflow integration distinguishes Nabla from standalone transcription tools that require manual copy-paste into the EHR. The platform supports over 85 medical specialties and multiple languages, making it practical across diverse clinical settings.\n\nFor physicians spending two or more hours per day on documentation, Nabla addresses one of the most significant sources of administrative burden and clinician burnout. The AI handles the transcription and note-structuring overhead, leaving the physician to focus on patient interaction and clinical reasoning. Nabla is HIPAA compliant and processes audio locally where possible to minimise data exposure.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=nabla.com&sz=64',
  'https://nabla.com',
  'https://nabla.com',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'paid',
  false,
  99.00,
  4.7,
  312,
  false, false, false,
  ARRAY['Generates structured SOAP notes automatically from conversation', 'Integrates directly with Epic, Cerner, and major EHR systems', 'Supports 85+ medical specialties and multiple languages', 'HIPAA compliant with local audio processing option', 'Significantly reduces post-visit documentation time'],
  ARRAY['Subscription cost adds to existing EHR licensing expenses', 'AI accuracy requires physician review before signing off', 'Initial specialty-specific training period needed for best output'],
  ARRAY['Automated clinical note generation during patient consultations', 'After-visit summary creation for patient communication', 'Referral letter drafting from consultation transcripts']
