(
  'abridge',
  'Abridge',
  'AI medical conversation summarisation for health systems',
  E'Abridge is an enterprise AI platform that captures and summarises medical conversations for health systems and large clinical groups. The technology is designed for deployment at scale: Abridge integrates into Epic''s Suki and Haiku workflows, allowing health systems to deploy AI documentation across entire physician groups without custom implementation for each clinician.\n\nAbridge''s AI generates structured clinical summaries, patient-facing after-visit summaries, and follow-up instructions from recorded consultations. The platform is built for ambient use  -  it runs in the background of a consultation without requiring the physician to interact with additional software during the visit. The focus on Epic integration and enterprise deployment distinguishes Abridge from consumer-facing tools: it is designed for health system IT procurement rather than individual physician subscription.\n\nAbridge has partnered with UPMC, Stanford Health Care, and several major health systems, giving it significant real-world validation data. The platform is trained on a large corpus of medical language and specialises in clinical accuracy rather than general transcription quality. For health system Chief Medical Information Officers evaluating ambient AI, Abridge is one of the strongest enterprise options available.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=abridge.com&sz=64',
  'https://abridge.com',
  'https://abridge.com',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'paid',
  false,
  0.00,
  4.8,
  198,
  false, false, false,
  ARRAY['Enterprise Epic integration at health system scale', 'Trained specifically on medical language for clinical accuracy', 'Partnership validation from UPMC, Stanford, and major systems', 'Generates both clinician notes and patient-facing summaries', 'Ambient operation requires no mid-consultation interaction'],
  ARRAY['Enterprise pricing and procurement  -  not available for individual physicians', 'Implementation requires IT coordination with health system', 'Less flexibility for solo practices or small groups'],
  ARRAY['Health system-wide clinical documentation automation', 'Epic EHR workflow integration for physician groups', 'Patient after-visit summary generation at scale']
),

(
  'suki-ai',
  'Suki AI',
  'AI voice assistant for physician documentation',
  E'Suki AI is a voice-based clinical documentation assistant that lets physicians dictate notes, retrieve patient information, and navigate EHR workflows using natural spoken commands. Rather than typing into an EHR or using a traditional transcription service, physicians speak naturally and Suki converts speech into structured clinical documentation.\n\nSuki differentiates from ambient documentation tools by supporting interactive voice commands during and after consultations: physicians can ask Suki to pull up a patient''s medication list, review prior diagnoses, or navigate to specific EHR sections without touching a keyboard. The AI learns individual physician preferences and documentation styles over time, improving accuracy and reducing review time as usage increases.\n\nSuki integrates with over 30 EHR systems including Epic, Cerner, and Meditech. The platform is HIPAA compliant and designed for deployment across single practices and large health systems. Google has invested in Suki, which has accelerated development of its AI capabilities and infrastructure. For physicians who find ambient passive recording systems less intuitive than active voice interaction, Suki''s command-driven approach offers a familiar dictation upgrade with AI structuring on top.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=suki.ai&sz=64',
  'https://suki.ai',
  'https://suki.ai',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'paid',
  false,
  0.00,
  4.6,
  445,
  false, false, false,
  ARRAY['Interactive voice commands for EHR navigation during consultations', 'Learns individual physician style over time', 'Integrates with 30+ EHR systems including Epic and Cerner', 'HIPAA compliant with Google infrastructure backing', 'Reduces typing burden across note creation and EHR navigation'],
  ARRAY['Voice-first approach requires adjustment for physicians used to typing', 'Custom pricing  -  no public per-seat rate', 'Command accuracy depends on environment noise levels'],
