(
  'corti',
  'Corti',
  'AI clinical decision support for emergency and primary care',
  E'Corti is an AI platform for clinical decision support that listens to patient-clinician conversations and provides real-time guidance to support diagnostic accuracy. Originally developed for emergency dispatch  -  where Corti detects signals of cardiac arrest in 999 and 911 calls before the caller describes it explicitly  -  the platform has expanded into primary care and acute settings.\n\nThe core capability is pattern recognition in spoken medical conversations. Corti''s AI identifies clinical red flags, suggests follow-up questions the clinician may have missed, and flags when conversation patterns resemble serious conditions that warrant immediate action. This real-time guidance layer helps less experienced clinicians and supports consistent protocol adherence across large provider organisations.\n\nCorti also generates structured documentation from consultations and integrates with EHR systems for note transfer. The emergency dispatch use case is particularly validated: Corti has processed millions of emergency calls across European health systems and demonstrated measurable improvements in cardiac arrest detection rates. For health systems focused on reducing diagnostic errors and improving triage consistency, Corti''s decision support capability addresses a different problem than documentation tools alone.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=corti.ai&sz=64',
  'https://corti.ai',
  'https://corti.ai',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'paid',
  false,
  0.00,
  4.5,
  167,
  false, false, false,
  ARRAY['Real-time clinical decision support during live consultations', 'Validated in emergency dispatch for cardiac arrest detection', 'Pattern recognition flags missed red flags and follow-up questions', 'Deployed at scale across European health systems', 'Generates structured documentation alongside decision support'],
  ARRAY['Enterprise deployment model  -  not suited for individual practice', 'Real-time AI guidance requires clinician trust in the system', 'Implementation and training investment required'],
  ARRAY['Emergency medical dispatch with AI triage support', 'Primary care consultation support for diagnostic consistency', 'Health system-wide protocol adherence monitoring']
),

(
  'regard',
  'Regard',
  'AI platform for hospital medicine and inpatient documentation',
  E'Regard is an AI clinical documentation and decision support tool built specifically for hospital medicine  -  the management of inpatients by hospitalists and internal medicine physicians. Where most AI documentation tools focus on outpatient primary care, Regard addresses the distinct complexity of inpatient charts: multiple active problems, evolving daily assessments, care coordination notes, discharge summaries, and complex medication reconciliation.\n\nRegard''s AI reads the full inpatient chart  -  labs, medications, prior notes, vitals, imaging results  -  and automatically generates a structured daily progress note that reflects the current clinical picture. The physician reviews and edits rather than writing from scratch. The AI also surfaces potential diagnoses the physician may want to consider based on the totality of chart data, functioning as a passive second-read on complex cases.\n\nRegard integrates directly with Epic and was initially validated at major academic medical centres. The platform targets the specific documentation burden of hospitalist medicine, where daily progress notes on every active patient create substantial writing overhead and where chart review across complex inpatients is time-consuming. For hospital medicine groups evaluating AI documentation, Regard addresses a gap that ambient conversation tools do not fully cover.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=regardhealth.com&sz=64',
  'https://regardhealth.com',
  'https://regardhealth.com',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'paid',
  false,
  0.00,
  4.6,
  124,
  false, false, false,
  ARRAY['Built specifically for inpatient hospital medicine workflows', 'Reads entire chart context to generate accurate progress notes', 'Surfaces diagnostic considerations from complex chart data', 'Epic integration for direct note insertion', 'Reduces daily progress note writing time for hospitalists'],
  ARRAY['Focused on inpatient/hospitalist medicine  -  limited outpatient utility', 'Enterprise procurement model  -  not for individual use', 'AI note review still requires physician sign-off for accuracy'],
  ARRAY['Daily hospital progress note generation for hospitalists', 'Complex inpatient chart review and documentation', 'Discharge summary drafting from full admission chart']
),

(
  'glass-health',
  'Glass Health',
  'AI clinical reasoning and differential diagnosis tool',
  E'Glass Health is an AI tool for clinical reasoning  -  physicians describe a patient presentation and Glass generates a structured differential diagnosis list, ranked by likelihood, with supporting reasoning for each entry. The tool is designed as a thinking partner for clinical decision-making rather than a documentation assistant.\n\nBeyond differential generation, Glass creates full clinical assessment and plan drafts, orders plans, and discharge instructions from a case summary. The AI is trained on medical literature and case data, producing outputs that reflect current clinical guidelines rather than generic text generation. Glass explains its reasoning for each differential entry, which makes it useful for learning (medical students and residents) and for double-checking clinical reasoning (experienced physicians reviewing complex presentations).\n\nGlass is lighter-weight than enterprise platforms: it runs in a web interface and mobile app without EHR integration requirements, making it accessible to individual physicians, residents, and medical students without IT procurement. The platform has gained significant adoption in medical education contexts where faculty use it to demonstrate clinical reasoning workflows alongside case discussions.',
  'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=glass.health&sz=64',
  'https://glass.health',
  'https://glass.health',
  ARRAY['healthcare'],
  'freemium',
  true,
  0.00,
