(
  'aidoc',
  'Aidoc',
  'AI radiology triage and clinical imaging workflow',
  E'Aidoc is an AI medical imaging analysis platform that reviews CT scans, MRIs, and X-rays in the background of normal radiology workflow, flagging critical findings  -  pulmonary embolisms, intracranial haemorrhages, aortic dissections, spinal fractures  -  in near real time so they can be prioritised before a radiologist reads the full study queue. The AI does not replace radiologist interpretation; it acts as a continuous background monitor that ensures critical findings are never buried in a full queue.\n\nAidoc is FDA-cleared for multiple indications including intracranial haemorrhage, pulmonary embolism, and incidental pulmonary nodule detection. FDA clearance is significant in AI radiology: it means clinical validation data has been reviewed and the tool can be used as part of clinical workflow rather than purely for research. Over 1,000 hospitals globally use Aidoc.\n\nThe platform integrates with PACS (Picture Archiving and Communication Systems) used in radiology departments and surfaces findings to both radiologists and clinical teams through notifications and integrated dashboards. For radiology departments handling high volumes of cross-sectional imaging, Aidoc addresses the triage problem: ensuring that the most time-sensitive findings receive the fastest attention regardless of when they arrive in the queue.',
